&lt;p&gt;An excited opportunity to Join the Advanced nurse practitioner team within the Trauma and Orthopeadics directorate at UHD has become available due to retirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would be based on the Bournemouth site initially with the possibility of cross site working as required due to the merge of the two hospital sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an highly motivated and experienced Advanced Nurse Practitioner, acting within your professional boundaries, you will provide care for our patients from initial history taking through clinical assessment, diagnosis, treatment and evaluation of care. You will demonstrate safe, clinical decision-making and deliver expert care. We require flexibility to meet the needs of the service, The role is full time 37.5 hours per week (Monday-Friday)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would join an already established team at RBH based within Orthopaedic outpatients, The role is predominantly focused on the pre assessment of patients awaiting elective Orthopaedic surgery and includes rotation onto the Orthopaedic wards to support the teams in caring for pre and post operative patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust have now merged into the University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: 30th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cathy Cocorachio, Matron  cathy.cocorachio@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0300 019 4375&lt;/p&gt;
